a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:9;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:9:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:96;s:5:"title";s:45:"Spiro separates Merge and Delete permissions";s:4:"href";s:74:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/spiro-separates-merge-and-delete-permissions/";s:13:"href-original";s:74:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/spiro-separates-merge-and-delete-permissions/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1770307421;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1770307417;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:355:"<p>Spiro now treats merge and delete as distinct permissions. This allows admins to delegate deduplication/cleanup workflows (merge) while restricting irreversible actions (delete).</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://support.spiro.ai/article/648-spiro-release-january-2026">https://support.spiro.ai/article/648-spiro-release-january-2026</a></p>
